com.delphix.masking.api.plugin.utils

Class ComponentChecker

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.delphix.masking.api.plugin.utils.ComponentChecker

  • public final class ComponentChecker
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides a method to check whether a component implements the MaskingAlgorithm interface, and if so, which data type it masks. In the future, methods will be added to discover the dependencies of components on other objects such as algorithms or files.

        public static MaskingAlgorithm.MaskingType getMaskingType(MaskingComponent obj)
        Determines the data type supported by the MaskingAlgorithm interface, and validates that the correct, matching ValueMetadata type parameter was chosen.
        Parameters:
        obj - The object to be evaluated
        Returns:
        The class name of the data type supported for masking, or null if the object doesn't implement the MaskingAlgorithm interface.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - When the object implements an invalid MaskingAlgorithm type

      • validateMultiColumnAssignment

        public static void validateMultiColumnAssignment(MaskingAlgorithm<GenericDataRow> algorithm,
                                                 java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> actualFields)
        Validate the set of logical fields for a multi-column algorithm masking assignment. This includes checking that all required fields are present, and all fields present are expected by the algorithm. An exception is thrown when the masking assignment is invalid.
        Parameters:
        algorithm - The multi-column algorithm to check
        actualFields - The set of logical fields that have been assigned in the masking assignment
        Since:
        1.9

      • validateMultiColumnAssignment

        public static void validateMultiColumnAssignment(java.lang.String algorithmName,
                                                 java.util.Collection<AlgorithmLogicalField> logicalFields,
                                                 java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> actualFields)
        Validate the set of logical fields for a multi-column algorithm masking assignment. This includes checking that all required fields are present, and all fields present are expected by the algorithm. This variant of the method exists to support the case where the expected field set has been cached, and avoids the work to load the plugin and instantiate the algorithm to perform the validation. An exception is thrown when the masking assignment is invalid.
        Parameters:
        algorithmName - The name of the algorithm
        logicalFields - The set of logical fields expected by the algorithm
        actualFields - The set of logical fields that have been assigned in the masking assignment
        Throws:
        InvalidMaskingAssignmentException - When the multi-column assignment is invalid
        Since:
        1.9
